            "commit": "586be217d8fe1617702571e18c324d29df27a6a8",
            "subject": "LU-9332 tests: fix pool_list issue in conf-sanity test_82b"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-03-07 21:34:36.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-04-23 03:11:41.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9319 statahead: skip agl for the file in restoring",
        "message": "LU-9319 statahead: skip agl for the file in restoring\n\nIn case of restore, the MDT has the right size and has already sent\nit back without granting the layout lock, inode is up-to-date. Then\nAGL (async glimpse lock) is useless.\n\nAlso to glimpse we need the layout, in case of a running restore the\nMDT holds the layout lock so the glimpse will block up to the end of\nrestore (statahead/agl will block).\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iaaf138a28671c3eccfb05b08ce8d7364423256a1\nReviewed-by: Lai Siyao <lai.siyao@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/26501\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
